    <string name="erasing_a_text" tools:ignore="StringEscaping"> To erase a text, hold down the text you want to erase and press "YES".</string>
    <string name="where_to_find">Files are saved on the root of the internal storage of the device in a folder named "Texts". You can add .txt files to this folder and they will appear in the app.</string>
    <string name="googledrive_sync" tools:ignore="StringEscaping"> If you linked your Google account to this app, you could use the "Sync" and "Download" options on the expandable menu.\nWith "Sync" you can upload and overwrite the ".txt" files on the "EditME" folder on your Google Drive. With "Download" you could download the ".txt" files from the "EditME" folder.\nThe "EditME" folder is created the first time you either use "Download" or "Upload".\n\nIt is important to notify that the "Download" option can only download ".txt" files that were created from this app.</string>
